  "body": "\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nIt happens to both justified epoch and finalized epoch when the start slot of epoch is missed. This is what I get\r\n```\r\nEpoch 2 is justified at root 0x04e951bd1a58c7f52e26a07b475b7e59bac3f3d80f2c0baac2748545c7886f80!\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is the log at end of Epoch 1 and start of Epoch 2\r\n```\r\n2020-07-08 15:37:29  [CHAIN]            info: Processed new chain head newChainHeadRoot=0xeba3c7dec48fe9ad8a2392f46b6a871fb5355550e73d5b5b28a5fac44c0845eb, slot=62, epoch=1\r\n2020-07-08 15:37:29  [CHAIN]            info: Processed new chain head newChainHeadRoot=0x04e951bd1a58c7f52e26a07b475b7e59bac3f3d80f2c0baac2748545c7886f80, slot=63, epoch=1\r\n2020-07-08 15:37:31  [CHAIN]            info: Processed new chain head newChainHeadRoot=0x471e17ac8d154a1cf982804140f1841477b024b6fa6c8d20064428642dfce13a, slot=65, epoch=2\r\n```\r\nWe can see that block 64 is missing.\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nThe justified block of epoch 2 should be `0x471e17ac8d154a1cf982804140f1841477b024b6fa6c8d20064428642dfce13a` which is the first slot of Epoch 2 (slot 65)\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n+ Print roots at https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/lodestar/src/chain/blocks/post.ts#L68 - `newJustifiedEpoch` and `newFinalizedEpoch` functions.\r\n+ Sync Altona until Epoch 3/4 to see the logs.\r\n\r\n",
