    "body": "Not a bug as explained by proto:\r\n```\r\nthat's normal\r\nOr occasionally, at least\r\nIt refers to the first block in  an epoch. If there's a skip slot at the first slot in that epoch, it will refer to the last known block in the chain\r\nThis is also the reason why checkpoint types are \"block root + epoch\". Checkpoints can continue, even though there may not be any blocks\r\n```",
